# Dart Coding Standards

## General Guidelines
- Follow the official [Dart style guide](https://dart.dev/guides/language/effective-dart/style)
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Keep functions small and focused on a single responsibility
- Add appropriate documentation comments for public APIs

## Flutter Specific
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Extract reusable widgets to separate files
- Use const constructors whenever possible
- Organize imports in the following order:
  1. Dart SDK imports
  2. Flutter imports
  3. Third-party package imports
  4. Local imports (using relative paths)

## State Management
- Use Riverpod or Provider for state management
- Keep business logic separate from UI code
- Avoid using setState for complex state management

## Models
- Implement proper equality and hashCode methods
- Include copyWith methods for immutability support
- Implement toJson and fromJson methods for serialization